The time has come to tear down our bedroom. The last room of the house where nothing has been done, just a little decoration.
Remove the horrible electric fireplace and mantel. Frame the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and sand it. Make a custom closet.
We always start with a quick pencil sketch...
The dirty step is finished.
I found several dead birds at the back of the chimney; all dried out :(
Ready for the plastering next week
Happy about the little nook on the side.
Insert the new wardrobe here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought about adding a charming little ventilation grill to prevent the chimney from taking in moisture.
The chimney sweep took care of installing the chimney cap and wind deflector. This should be a bit safer for the crows who nest up there 🪶
The plasterer is done. We will install the floor tomorrow!
The cork layer is laid down, I improvised a wood dust extractor using a roll of toilet paper as an accessory for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Part of the planks is sorted and ready to lay. We're just taking a tea break.
OK, the progress has been slow today due to delicate cuts around the door frames to achieve a smooth transition to the corridor (which is also being installed). @user45@twitter.com has cursed.
Finished, but on my knees! The final touch: incomprehensible instructions for setting up the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
The corridor floor and all the baseboards still need to be done. The decorator is coming in a month, so for now, at home, it's bare plaster that looks chic.
A small evening DIY session to remove the lower sections of the door frames with a tenon saw or coping saw at the point where we want the floor to fit perfectly.
The cork underlayer in the hallway is also installed.
We finished the corridor floor yesterday! Then we left at 5 am this morning to go pick up Thing 1 from Heathrow, then we had a nap and it's the final stretch for the corridor; baseboards installed. We'll take care of the sealing when the glue has set.
